The paper focuses on emotion recognition from facial expressions, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) research. The use of adversarial autoencoders and personalized affective memories also suggests a focus on generative models and human-computer interaction, which are relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories.
